  "description": "Sigurd Dahllöf was a Swedish writer known for his works of poetry, fairy tales and short stories. He was also a member of the Swedish Writers' Association and the Gothenburg Authors' Association. Dahllöf was born on May 5, 1877, in Trollhättan, Sweden to Tell D. and Tekla Berggren, both of whom were in the forestry profession. He married Karin Hansson in 1927 and had a son named Urban in 1928. Dahllöf worked as an accountant at Sandvikens Jernverks A-B, See Fabr. A-B, Ax. Hofstedt forwarding firm, and A-B Hallins Art Gallery. He later became a writer and an assistant at the Gothenburg Harbor Commission. Dahllöf was also an amateur astronomer." 
